com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Sat 25 Aug 2007</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg" class="newsbody"><a name="32377"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Gender Issues in Gaming</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/104274373">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=32377>Print News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Do women want different things in games than men do?  The Executive Producer of Her Interactive, which makes the Nancy Drew series of games targeted at teenage girls, <a href="http://videogames.yahoo.com/news-527586">says they do.</a> Speaking at the Game Convention currently going on in Liepzig, Germany, Robert Riedl believes women and girls want a game that is based in reality, not fantasy, and has a strong storyline, among other elements.<br><br>Read the entire article below.<br><br>I think there's a lot of interesting ideas in this news report.  Check out what I think about it in this <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/View.php?view=Columns.Detail&id=56&category_select_id=6">Kwill's Quill: Gender Issues in Video Games.</a></span><p><a href="fullstory.php?id=32377">Read More...</a><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Sat 25 Aug 2007</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Fri 24 Aug 2007</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg" class="newsbody"><a name="32365"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Secrets of Faydwer Lore</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/104268382">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=32365>Print News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Get the skinny on the <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/news_article.vm?id=50540">lore behind the next EQ expansion,</a> Secrets of Faydwer, and check out the screenshots.<br><br>"The clockwork armies of the evil gnomish necromancer Meldrath the Malignant gather in the Steamfont Mountains, awaiting his order to invade the kingdom of Ak'Anon. The launch of his great air fortress Mechanotus has torn open the earth, exposing new paths into unexplored regions of the ancient continent of Faydwer. <br><br>Rediscover Faydwer as you adventure in the nearby Loping Plains, home to the soul eating wereorcs of Bloodmoon Keep. Strive to end the torment of humans and elves cursed for centuries in the Hills of Shade. All the while, an ancient menace stirs east of the Dragonscale Hills, where the prismatic dragon Kerafyrm the Awakened plans his revenge. "<br><br>On an interesting note, those who play EQII will recognize the Loping Plains as a zone name from that game -- also the home of some of Faydwer's werewolves and vampires.</span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Fri 24 Aug 2007</span><br><br><br><a name="32354"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Producer Notes</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/104263467">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=32354>Print News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Clint Worley has posted some comments on various player concerns in <a href="http://forums.station.sony.com/eq/posts/list.m?topic_id=117794">Producer Tidbits</a> on EQPlayers.  Maybe some of your questions will be answered!</span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Fri 24 Aug 2007</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Thu 23 Aug 2007</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg" class="newsbody"><a name="32336"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Legends of Norrath Beta Accepting More</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/104255942">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=32336>Print News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Clint Worley posted:<br><br>We are accepting an additional limited number of players into the LoN Beta. The timing on this invitation is tight so hurry if you want to get in. We will be ranodmly selecting people that register. Good luck!<br><br>Here are the details...<br><br>Interested in getting into Legends of Norrath beta?<br><br>If you're interested in joining into the Legends of Norrath beta please send an email with the subject LON to eq2beta@station.sony.com , and that email should only contain just your account name.<br><br>*Please Note* This covers both EverQuest and EverQuest 2 players even though the address says eq2beta.<br><br>Go check out the <a href="http://legendsofnorrath.station.sony.com/">LoN message boards<a/> to learn more about the game!</span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Thu 23 Aug 2007</span><br><br><br><a name="32335"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">EverQuest in MSNBC's Top Five Addictive Games</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/104255889">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=32335>Print News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">Coming in at number two, EverQuest was <a href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/20398361/?pg=3#games_top5_070822">voted one of the top five</a> most addictive games by MSNBC's Ken Smith.  I think that's a good thing ... although I believe we aren't using the word "addicted" anymore, are we?  "Inappropriate play habits" is the term now, so I hear.<br><br>My other gripe is referring to EQ in the past tense by the author ["The game, which shipped in 1999, <strong>was</strong> hugely popular with players and critics alike"], when it's still getting bigger and better, and is just as addictive as ever!</span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Thu 23 Aug 2007</span><br><br><br><a name="32327"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Developer Chat Logs for August 21</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/0">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=32327>Print News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">This month's Stratic's developer chat was chock-full of information, and you can read the entire log below.<br><br>Highlights include:<br><br>*Ronda* In the next expansion, when the magicians get a new mana rod, can the color of it be more distintive than brown?  Many times people have sat down to mem new spells and couldn't because they are holding an elemental rod on their pointer and don't notice it.<br><br>Prathun: Yes, definitely. I'd like to change the visual look of the rod in the next expansion, both the held graphic and the icon so it doesn't look like a Harry Potter wand.<br><br>*Swampfunk* What is SOE's current plan to balance 2handed weapons between Berserkers and Everyone Else?<br><br>Merloc: Two-handed weapons are something that I am currently looking into.  There are several factors that play into balance, and I have several options that I'm considering, including splitting berserkers away from the other classes, although I am reluctant to do that.<br><br>*CopyMS* Are there any plans to give Mages additional functionality with the new expansion?<br><br>Prathun: I've got a few new spells in mind for all classes, and we're going to be looking at the survivability and general contribution of pets across the board.<br><br>*Kristin* In response to the August 12th Producer’s Letter, many threads have popped up around the community forums discussing and showing a strong interest in Alternate Rule Set Servers.  Given the popularity of the Progression Servers and the great job that Maddoc and the team did; have the Developers made any progress that you could talk about, or do you have any feedback as to when a server such as this might become available?<br><br>Rashere: Right now, we're just gauging interest to see what people would like to see.  I'm glad to see people like the idea.  We don't have any concrete plans to announce yet on what a new, alternate rule server would be or when it might occur though.<br><br>*Croix_FV* With Secrets of Faydwer around the corner, rumors are of course popping up regarding the level of gear. Is there any definite info yet about that, and what effect do you plan on SoF gear/levels having on past expansion content?<br><br>Merloc: I don't want to go into the details of the specific numbers, but for single group content there will be 3.5 tiers of loot above Praetorian gear in TBS, for raiders there will be 2 Tiers of loot above Solteris. In TBS, there were 1.5 tiers for single group, and 1 tier for raiders over the previous expansion.<br><br>*Parollee* Any reasoning behind wizards not being able to have a prismatic familiar? even one with no stats and less of a focus?<br><br>Nodyin: A "Prismatic" familiar that was near the focus level of the familiars that wizards currently have (even a 20% focus) would be very powerful. It would essentially mean a blanket increase in power - there would be no reason to have any other familiar up and you'd have it up all the time.  If the focus was low enough not to be overpowered it would be "useless." There's no good way to implement that. Also the basic design of the familiars is based on forcing a Wizard to *choose* one area of expertise to focus on. There are no plans for a Prismatic familiar.<br><br>*fcseven* for prathun Is there a chance for necros to have no illusion while liched or a new illusion for Sof,the skelly is geting old.<br><br>Prathun: It's something Rytan always wanted to add in - a way to optionally choose if you wanted to be in an illusion form while liched or just yourself - I think it's something we can get in for SoF.</span><p><a href="fullstory.php?id=32327">Read More...</a><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Thu 23 Aug 2007</span><br><br><br><a name="32325"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Beta Sign Ups</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/104251672">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=32325>Print News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">The opportunity to be in the beta for Secrets of Faydwer may be coming up again.  If you have an interest in helping test out the next expansion, keep checking <a href="https://store.station.sony.com/eqbeta/index.jsp">here</a> for an invitation.  If the "key required" page comes up, it means the beta sign-ups are closed for the time being.</span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Thu 23 Aug 2007</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Wed 22 Aug 2007</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg" class="newsbody"><a name="32276"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">SOE at GenCon</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/104234212">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=32276>Print News</a></span><br><span class="newsbody">EverQuest and other SOE titles were well represented at GenCon 2007, and I got to take a look at the newest EQ expansion, Secrets of Faydwer.  The "best four days in gaming" now include your favorite digital games, as well.  Check out my visit in <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/static.php?page=soegencon">SOE Helps GenCon Enter the Digital Age</a>.</span><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Wed 22 Aug 2007</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--></center>
